cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper is primarily focused on the capacity and complexity of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new notion of capacity based on Information Geometry, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The experiments conducted in the paper are on image classification tasks, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the generalization error of the proposed measure, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning theory (cs.SI).
